{
  "slug": "embeddings-are-compression-with-opinions",
  "title": "Embeddings are compression with opinions",
  "category": "ai",
  "kicker": "AI fundamentals",
  "hook": "An embedding turns messy meaning into numbers. That is useful, but it is not neutral, magic, or guaranteed to match how your users think.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-20",
  "tags": [
    "embeddings",
    "search"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Similarity is a product choice",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Vector search feels objective because it returns scores. But those scores come from a model trained to notice some kinds of similarity more than others. Your corpus, chunking, and user language decide whether that is helpful.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "search · weird neighbors",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "$ search \"cancel appointment fee\"",
              "c": "pr"
            },
            {
              "t": "0.82 cancellation policy",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "0.79 appointment reminders",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "0.76 subscription cancelation typo page",
              "c": "dim"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Look at the neighbors",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Do not tune embeddings from aggregate scores alone. Inspect nearest neighbors for real queries, label misses, and decide which mistakes matter to the product.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "evals/nearest-neighbors.js",
          "code": "for (const query of evalQueries) {\n  const hits = await vector.search(query, { topK: 5 });\n  console.log(query, hits.map((h) => h.slug));\n}",
          "caption": "A simple neighbor dump can explain a lot of strange answers."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Pair vectors with old-school filters",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Metadata filters, keyword search, recency rules, and reranking can make vector search less mysterious. The best retrieval systems are usually hybrids.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "stats",
          "items": [
            {
              "to": 5,
              "label": "neighbors worth inspecting per query"
            },
            {
              "to": 2,
              "label": "search modes: vector plus keyword"
            },
            {
              "to": 1,
              "label": "human-labeled eval set"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "04 · the takeaway",
      "heading": "Numbers still need judgment",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Embeddings are powerful because they compress meaning. They are risky for the same reason. Keep the compression visible.</p>"
        },
